TASK_TITLE=CRITICAL: Fix Task Reviewer spin loop — burns tokens endlessly on ACTIVE_TASKS wake
TASK_STATUS=done
TASK_TYPE=bug
TASK_CREATED_BY=boss
TASK_TEAM=W2
TASK_DESCRIPTION=The Task Reviewer (pane 1.1) is stuck in a devastating spin loop that burns tokens continuously:

1. reviewer-wait.sh wakes with WAKE_REASON=ACTIVE_TASKS
2. Reviewer checks messages — finds none
3. Goes back to reviewer-wait.sh
4. Immediately wakes again on ACTIVE_TASKS
5. Repeat forever — 29+ minutes of token burn observed

ROOT CAUSE: reviewer-wait.sh triggers on ACTIVE_TASKS existing, but the Reviewer has no work to do for those tasks (they need deployment, not review, or are already reviewed). The wake condition is too broad.

FIX REQUIREMENTS:
- reviewer-wait.sh must NOT wake on ACTIVE_TASKS alone — it should only wake when there's an actual review request message for the reviewer
- When there are no review messages, the Reviewer must SLEEP indefinitely (not poll)
- The Reviewer agent prompt should instruct: if no review messages found after waking, go back to sleep immediately without entering a monitoring loop
- Kill the current spinning Reviewer process immediately
- This is task #452 revisited — the previous fix (bfe7673) was insufficient

Files: shell/reviewer-wait.sh (or hooks/reviewer-wait.sh), agents/doey-task-reviewer.md.tmpl
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W2.1: Research reviewer-wait.sh and doey-task-reviewer.md.tmpl — report full contents and wake logic:done\n2:W2.1: Fix reviewer-wait.sh — remove ACTIVE_TASKS wake condition from _check_work():done\n3:W2.2: Update doey-task-reviewer.md.tmpl — remove observation loop, sleep when no messages:done\n4:W2.2: Verify both fixes — reviewer-wait.sh and doey-task-reviewer.md.tmpl:done
